 ### The application is generated in three layers: core, application, and
 infrastructure.
 .
 | **Layer** | **Main Responsibility** | **Knows About** | **Example Classes /
 Components** |
 |------------|-------------------------|------------------|-----------------------------------|
 | **Core (Domain)** | Contains the core business logic and entities. Defines
 domain rules, invariants, and pure data models — completely independent of
 frameworks. | None | `User`, `Order`, `Product`, `Payment`, `Money`, `Email` |
 | **Application** | Orchestrates use cases and coordinates the business logic
 using the domain entities. Handles transactions, validation, and flow control.
 | Core | `CreateUserService`, `ProcessPaymentUseCase`, `OrderManager`,
 `DtoMapper` |
 | **Infrastructure** | Implements the technical details and integrates with
 external systems (databases, APIs, file storage, messaging, etc.). Contains
 controllers, repositories, and configurations. | Application (and sometimes
 Core) | `UserRepositoryJpa`, `PaymentApiClient`, `EmailServiceImpl`,
 `UserController`, `SpringConfig` |
 .

